<example id="accs_runtime_integration">
<description>
Connecting Adobe Commerce as a Cloud Service (ACCS) and Adobe I/O Runtime Web Actions.
</description>
<code language="json">
// mesh.json
{
  "meshConfig": {
    "sources": [
      {
        "name": "ACCS_Commerce",
        "handler": {
          "graphql": {
            "endpoint": "https://na1-sandbox.api.commerce.adobe.com/{{env.ACCS_ENV_ID}}/graphql",
            "operationHeaders": {
              "x-api-key": "{{env.ACCS_API_KEY}}",
              "Magento-Website-Code": "{{env.ACCS_WEBSITE_CODE}}",
              "Magento-Customer-Group": "{{env.ACCS_CUSTOMER_GROUP}}",
              "Magento-Store-Code": "{{env.ACCS_STORE_CODE}}",
              "Magento-Store-View-Code": "{{env.ACCS_STORE_VIEW_CODE}}"
            },
            "schemaHeaders": {
              "x-api-key": "{{env.ACCS_API_KEY}}"
            }
          }
        },
        "transforms": [
          {
            "prefix": {
              "includeRootOperations": true,
              "includeTypes": false,
              "value": "accs_"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "IOActions",
        "handler": {
          "JsonSchema": {
            "baseUrl": "{{env.AIO_RUNTIME_BASE_URL}}",
            "operations": [
              {
                "type": "Query",
                "field": "hello",
                "path": "/actions/hello",
                "method": "GET",
                "responseTypeName": "HelloResponse"
              }
            ],
            "operationHeaders": {
              "Authorization": "Bearer {{env.AIO_RUNTIME_TOKEN}}"
            }
          }
        },
        "transforms": [
          {
            "prefix": {
              "includeRootOperations": true,
              "includeTypes": false,
              "value": "actions_"
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
</code>
<key_points>
- **ACCS Integration**: Requires specific headers (`Magento-Website-Code`, `x-api-key`, etc.) and dynamic endpoints using `ACCS_ENV_ID`.
- **Runtime Actions**: Served via `JsonSchema` handler. Actions must be web-enabled (`/api/v1/web`).
- **Env Vars**: Critical for managing tenant IDs, tokens, and store codes.
</key_points>
</example>

<example id="programmatic_resolver_batching">
<description>
A JS resolver demonstrating data fetching from sources, context usage, and a pattern for batching (conceptually).
</description>
<code language="javascript">
// resolvers/customResolver.js
module.exports = {
  Query: {
    enrichedData: async (root, args, context, info) => {
      // 1. Fetch basic data from one source
      const baseData = await context.sources.CustomRest.Query.getCustomData({
        args: { id: args.id }
      });

      // 2. Use context state for caching high-frequency data
      let extraInfo = await context.state.get(`info-${args.id}`);
      
      if (!extraInfo) {
        // 3. Fetch from another source if not cached
        // (Note: In a real batching scenario, you'd collect keys and fetch once)
        const commerceProduct = await context.sources.CommerceGraphQL.Query.commerce_products({
          args: { filter: { sku: { eq: baseData.sku } } },
          selectionSet: '{ items { name price_range { minimum_price { regular_price { value } } } } }'
        });
        
        extraInfo = commerceProduct.items[0] || {};
        
        // Cache for 10 minutes
        await context.state.put(`info-${args.id}`, JSON.stringify(extraInfo), { ttl: 600 });
      } else {
        extraInfo = JSON.parse(extraInfo);
      }

      return {
        ...baseData,
        commerceDetails: extraInfo
      };
    }
  }
};
</code>
</example>

<example id="declarative_resolver">
<description>
Mapping a query directly to a source operation without writing code.
</description>
<code language="json">
// Insert into mesh.json > meshConfig > additionalResolvers
{
  "Query": {
    "myQuickCart": {
      "type": "single",
      "source": "CommerceGraphQL",
      "operation": "commerce_cart",
      "mapArgs": {
        "cart_id": "args.id"
      }
    }
  }
}
</code>
